text:
52-56 East 67th Street, south side, east of Park Avenue.

About 1913.

International News.

Park Avenue at S. W. corner of 67th Street, showing The Sulgreve, a new apartment hotel at 56 East 67th Street. The old house on the corner will be demolished in the autumn of 1929, to make place for a garden for the hotel. About 1924.

655 Park Avenue, east side, from 67th to 68th Streets, showing the new Apartment building on the site of the old Hospital. Beyond it up Lenox Hill may be seen part of the Hunter College buildings. 1924.

Joseph Smith, Photographer.

Park Avenue, south on west side from 71st Street to 67th Street, on Lenox Hill, showing old Presbyterian Hospital between 71st and 70th, shortly before its demolition. On north west corner of 71st may be seen part of the G.S. Brewster residence, which will be demolished in 1929, and in the south west corner of 74th Street the George S. Blumenthal residence.

P.L. Sperr, Photographer.

View 2 is a duplicate of the above, mounted June 1973 with non-acidic glue, because the original print is deteriorating.

67th Street, south side, between Park and Lexington avenues. This apartment house was erected on the former site of the Baptist Home for the Aged. A.S. Thomas was the architect for the new building.

About 1930.

George H. Van Anda.
